        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 24 at 10:39PM CDT by NWS Huntsville AL</headline>
        <description>At 1038 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles south of Red Bay, moving north at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Pleasant Site, Pogo, Red Bay, Cedar Creek Reservoir, Atwood, Dempsey,
Vina, Little Bear Creek Reservoir, and Halltown.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
